source.Name: Total population
source.Summary: Population: Total population and distribution by age and sex estimated to be consistent with the population by age and sex of the (a) 1962, 1974, 1984, 2008, 2022 censuses; (b) adjusted for under/over count; (c) adjusted for age heaping; (d) adjusted for under enumeration of children under age 15; (e) 1970, 1971 PGS survey estimates; (f) official estimates through 2014; and with estimates of the subsequent trends in fertility, mortality and international migration. In addition, the 1986, 1999-2000, 2007, 2013, 2019-2020 DHS and 2009, 2011, 2016 MIS survey estimates have been considered.

source.Name: Total fertility rate
source.Summary: Fertility: Total fertility rate and age pattern of fertility based on: (a) birth-histories data from the 1986, 2007, 2013, 2019-2020 DHS and 2009, 2011, 2016, 2022 MIS; (b) births in the household in the preceding 12 (or 24) months classified by age of mother from the 1970, 1971 PGS; (c) adjusted fertility using Brass P/F ratio method (or variants) with data on children ever born and births in the preceding 12 (or 24/36) months, both classified by age of mother, from the 1970 PGS and 1974, 1984, 2008 censuses; (d) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1962, 1974, 1984, 2008 censuses and 1970, 1971 PGS; (e) cohort-completed fertility backdated by the mean age of childbearing from the 1970, 1971 PGS and 1974, 1984 censuses and 1986, 2013, 2019-2020 DHS and 2009, 2011, 2016 MIS. In addition, the (a) official estimates of age-specific fertility rates through 2014; (b) births in the household in the preceding 12 (or 24) months classified by age of mother from the 1984, 2008 censuses; (c) adjusted fertility using Brass P/F ratio method (or variants) with data on children ever born and births in the preceding 12 (or 24/36) months, both classified by age of mother, from the 1971 PGS; (d) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1955-2010 Education Stats and 2011, 2016 MIS; (e) cohort-completed fertility backdated by the mean age of childbearing from the 2007 DHS and 2008 Census have been considered.

source.Name: Life expectancy at birth
source.Summary: Overall Mortality: Life expectancy at birth and age pattern of mortality based on: (a) registered deaths by age and sex available through 2008; (b) The demographic impact of AIDS has been factored into the mortality estimates; (c) estimates using HIV/AIDS model life tables and estimates of under-five mortality (5q0), and adult mortality (45q15). Mortality rates for Spectrum were calculated by removing AIM's estimates of HIV-related mortality from all-cause mortality rate estimates published in the 2024 revision of the World Population Prospects.

source.Name: Age Mortality
source.Summary: Adult and Old Age Mortality: Estimates derived from: (a) recent household deaths data by age and sex from the 1970 PGS; (b) siblings deaths from the 2007, 2013, 2019-2020 DHS; (c) maternal orphanhood from the 2007, 2013, 2019-2020 DHS and 2008 Census; (d) paternal orphanhood from the 2007, 2013, 2019-2020 DHS and 2008 Census; (e) intercensal survivorship from successive census age distributions; (f) estimates of under-five, adult and old age mortality. In addition, the recent household deaths data by age and sex from the 2008 Census have been considered.

source.Name: Infant/child mortality
source.Summary: Child Mortality: Under-five mortality based on: (a) registered infant and child deaths through 2008; (b) direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 1971 PGS and 1986, 2007, 2013, 2019-2020 DHS and 2009 MIS; (c) indirect estimates from data on children ever born and surviving from the 1971 PGS and 2011, 2016 MIS; (d) International estimates used up to 2021. In addition, the (a) direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 1970 PGS and 1999-2000 DHS; (b) indirect estimates from data on children ever born and surviving from the 1974, 2008 censuses; (c) recent household deaths from the 1978 NDS and 2008 Census have been considered.

source.Name: International migration
source.Summary: Migration: International migration based on: (a) information on foreign-born populations from censuses and registers from major countries of destination; (b) estimates derived as the differences between overall population growth and natural increase; (c) UNHCR statistics on the number of refugees in the main countries of asylum.
